Usage: analyze_ir_paths [-help] -clock_period <float>
                        [-hierarchical_activity_file <string>]
                        [-max_slack <float>] [-pre_simulation_period <float>]
                        -seq_activity <float> -simulation_period <float>
                        [-user_defined_critical_paths <string>]

-help                                     # Prints out the command usage
-clock_period <float>                     # Period of dominant clock of the
                                          # design, in library time units
                                          # (float, required)
-hierarchical_activity_file <string>      # filename containing <hierarchy>
                                          # <activity> name pair(s)
                                          # (string, optional)
-max_slack <float>                        # Slack limit of endpoints to be
                                          # modeled, in library time units
                                          # (float, optional)
-pre_simulation_period <float>            # pre simulation duration, actual
                                          # start time of simulation
                                          # (float, optional)
-seq_activity <float>                     # Sequencial activity between [0-1]
                                          # (float, required)
-simulation_period <float>                # Duration of transient simulation,
                                          # in library time units
                                          # (float, required)
-user_defined_critical_paths <string>     # collection of criitcal paths to be
                                          # modeled on priority (string, optional)